rchase of empire kosher foods what eating healthy foods and keeping kosher have in common is watching what one eats paying attention where the food comes from and how it was raised it would seem the empire kosher would be a logical combination with hain celestials holistic offerings empire was already health conscious as well as kosher and features hormonefree humanely raised antibiotic free poultry in  empire kosher valley which featured sustainably raised fowl hain celestial purchased the  stake of empire kosher for  million it already owned  a stake in empire around   of hain celestial’s offerings even prior to the empire acquisition are kosher irwin simon told marketwatch “empire is a strong brand in a growing category with a lot of experience which provides us with the opportunity to broaden our existing portfolio of organic and natural brands into healthier kosher products empire should leverage hain celestial’s knowhow and infrastructure to pursue new categories and kosher product offerings” irwin simon’s father ran a kosher dairy store in nova scotia he was also a kosher butcher and used to slaughter the meat in the back simon told inc about his childhood “as a family five kids we all worked in the store and my father taught us work ethics how to treat people to work with people” simon often wondered why his father didn’t take more risks and expand his business but he certainly has taken risks and expanded with his own business hain celestial read more about businessfinance butcher economy of the united states empire company limited empire kosher food and drink hain irwin simon jewish cuisine kashrut kosher the hain celestial group inc related news most popular tags technology ceo business united states israeli new york jewish businessfinance people israel all rights reserved  terms  conditions  privacy policy  sitemap contact  subscribe  comment email delivered by feedburner microsoft personalized ad preferences to opt out of personalized ads in this browse